e of the American republic above all else. His failures as a statesman were, more often than not, the result of circumstances beyond his control, notably the weakness of the fledgling American republic in a world of warring empires.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCommunication in family planningzUganda. 0aHealth promotionzUganda. 0aJefferson, Thomas, -- 1743-1826. 0aMaternal health serviceszUganda. 0aUnited States -- Foreign relations -- 1801-1809. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Presidents & Heads of State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018244640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300182446423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300182446/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles